abstract: Jordan refuses to meet Islamic State's demand for release of militant Sajida al-Rishawi until militants show proof of life for captured Jordanian pilot First Lt Moaz al-Kasasbeh; standoff for prisoner swap raises fears that Kasasbeh, and captured Japanese journalist Kenji Goto, will be killed.
lead_paragraph: Jordan, which is willing to release an imprisoned militant, apparently has not received proof that its captured air force pilot, being held with a Japanese journalist, is still alive.

byline.original: By ROD NORDLAND and RANYA KADRI

snippet: Jordan, which is willing to release an imprisoned militant, apparently has not received proof that its captured air force pilot, being held with a Japanese journalist, is still alive.

headline.main: Jordan Lets Islamic State’s Deadline for a Prisoner Exchange Pass
